Labuanium politum

is known to be associated with the nipah palm (

Nypa fruticans

) (
Ng et al. 2015a
). 
Ng et al. (2015a)
also noted that the species has been occasionally found among mangrove tree roots with no nipah palm patches around the area (
Rahayu and Setyadi 2009
), although the specimens concerned may be vagrants.
